cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.RO 

The paper proposes a deep learning model that uses reinforcement learning to predict task-relevant locations in interactive environments. This involves processing visual input frames and learning to focus on the most pertinent parts of the input. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a deep learning model that uses reinforcement learning to learn how to predict where to look in interactive environments. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper involves processing visual input frames and predicting fixation locations, which falls under the scope of computer vision. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a model that uses reinforcement learning to learn how to predict task-relevant locations, which falls under the scope of artificial intelligence. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper involves predicting task-relevant locations in interactive environments, which is relevant to the field of human-computer interaction. 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper proposes a model that can be used to teach robots how to predict task-relevant locations in interactive environments, which falls under the scope of robotics.
